[SN]TITLE[SN]
England women suffer heavy defeat by Argentina at Olympic Park

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
England's women suffered a 5-1 home defeat by Argentina in an international match at the Olympic Park in London.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The visitors led early in the second period through a Agustina Habif goal but Hannah Martin levelled for England soon after.
Martina Cavallero put Argentina back in front before Magdalena Fernandez made it 3-1 for the team ranked third in the world.
Delfina Merino and Eugenia Trinchinetti scored to put the result beyond doubt.
England, who are ranked second in the world, face top-ranked side Holland on Sunday.
